WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:39.122 --> 00:41.623
[MAN COUGHING]

00:52.510 --> 00:55.137
[COUGHING]

01:26.211 --> 01:27.503
PORTER:
GSW.

01:28.963 --> 01:31.340
That's what the hospitals call it.

01:32.133 --> 01:33.926
Gunshot wound.

01:34.886 --> 01:38.180
Doctor has to report it
to the police.

01:39.349 --> 01:42.518
That makes it hard
for guys in my line to get...

01:43.520 --> 01:45.187
..."quality health care."

01:45.355 --> 01:47.689
[DOCTOR GRUNTS]

01:51.402 --> 01:54.530
PORTER: Not many men know
what their life's worth.

01:54.823 --> 01:55.948
I do.

01:56.407 --> 02:00.661
Seventy grand.
That's what they took from me.

02:01.246 --> 02:04.540
And that's what
I was going to get back.

02:29.732 --> 02:32.401
They say, "Time heals all wounds."

02:33.069 --> 02:36.655
You'd think, after five months
of lying on my back...

02:37.073 --> 02:40.033
...I'd give up
any idea of getting even.

02:40.243 --> 02:42.703
Just be a nice guy, call it a day.

02:45.081 --> 02:49.710
Nice guys are fine. You got to have
someone to take advantage of.

02:49.919 --> 02:51.712
But they always finish last.

02:51.880 --> 02:54.339
[BEGGAR SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

02:57.969 --> 03:00.846
BEGGAR: Help a cripple.
Thank you, sir.

03:01.264 --> 03:04.391
Help a Vietnam vet walk again.

03:06.603 --> 03:09.188
Help a cripple.
Thank you, sir.

03:09.397 --> 03:11.773
What the fuck you doing?
Get the fuck out!

03:11.941 --> 03:14.943
- Unh!
PORTER: Shut up. I cured you.

03:15.111 --> 03:17.154
[HOMELESS MAN COUGHS]

03:17.322 --> 03:18.447
Cocksucker.

03:24.120 --> 03:27.289
- What do I owe you?
- Two ninety-eight.

03:45.141 --> 03:48.393
Son of a...
Hey, my cigarettes!

04:21.302 --> 04:24.137
- Unh!
- Sorry, sorry. Pardon me.

04:45.868 --> 04:47.160
[SIGHS]

04:59.340 --> 05:00.549
Thank you.

05:05.680 --> 05:06.722
One hundred...

05:06.931 --> 05:08.181
...two hundred...

05:08.433 --> 05:09.725
...three hundred.

05:10.059 --> 05:12.019
Have a nice day, Mr. Johnson.

05:12.854 --> 05:14.730
Excellent fit, sir.

05:15.064 --> 05:16.815
And how will you be paying?

05:44.135 --> 05:45.427
[KNOCKS ON WINDOW]

05:45.595 --> 05:48.263
- Mister?
- Hmm?

05:49.766 --> 05:51.433
I'll give you $900.

05:51.976 --> 05:53.226
Let me see that Magnum.

05:57.690 --> 05:58.857
That's it.

06:22.590 --> 06:23.799
$500 and the gun.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.970
Uh, I'll need to see I.D.

06:29.514 --> 06:30.889
Of course.

06:44.695 --> 06:48.156
I'm sorry, Mr. Johnson, uh,
this card's been canceled.

06:48.491 --> 06:49.908
Impossible.

06:50.159 --> 06:52.911
Do you have another form
of payment?

06:53.162 --> 06:54.621
Try it again.

07:12.682 --> 07:14.599
[WOMAN COUGHING NEARBY]

07:44.672 --> 07:46.214
[WOMAN COUGHS]

07:54.682 --> 07:56.850
[COUGHING]

08:01.689 --> 08:03.857
[GRUNTS AND COUGHS]

08:04.901 --> 08:07.819
PORTER:
Old habits die hard, I guess.

08:08.863 --> 08:13.033
If you don't kick them,
they kick you.

08:14.243 --> 08:16.578
Ain't marriage grand?

08:41.020 --> 08:43.772
[WOMAN PANTING]

08:43.940 --> 08:45.232
Porter.

08:46.734 --> 08:48.568
You're not dead.

08:51.447 --> 08:53.448
What are you going to do?
Kill me?

09:30.653 --> 09:33.572
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING
GENTLE MELODY]

09:45.751 --> 09:47.085
[MUSIC STOPS]

10:01.809 --> 10:03.435
Not now.

10:04.562 --> 10:06.313
Yeah.

10:07.189 --> 10:08.356
You're cleaning up.

10:08.524 --> 10:10.525
[SIGHS]

10:33.799 --> 10:34.966
[LOCK CLICKS]

11:19.762 --> 11:21.054
[HORN HONKS OUTSIDE]

11:21.222 --> 11:22.472
[PORTER SIGHS]

11:25.184 --> 11:27.185
[SIGHS]

11:31.357 --> 11:33.024
[GRUNTS]

11:35.820 --> 11:44.119
[SIGHS]

12:22.825 --> 12:25.243
[PHONE RINGING]

12:37.173 --> 12:39.340
LYNN:
Val still wants to talk to you.

12:42.511 --> 12:44.137
Sorry, babe.

12:45.848 --> 12:48.516
Shall I tell him
to call back again?

12:49.185 --> 12:52.854
No, I'll talk to him.
Shut him up, anyway.

12:53.022 --> 12:54.898
[GROANS]

12:55.608 --> 12:57.233
Val.

12:58.527 --> 13:01.196
Yep, same as always. You?

13:01.489 --> 13:03.907
Yeah, good, good. Um...

13:04.658 --> 13:06.117
Why? Are you there now?

13:06.285 --> 13:08.119
[CHUCKLES]

13:09.872 --> 13:12.957
Don't sweat it, Val.
We all look alike to them.

13:15.252 --> 13:17.837
VAL: Same crew. The Chows.
Twice a week.

13:18.088 --> 13:22.217
Tuesday and Friday, between 11 and 12.
Always the same route.

13:22.760 --> 13:25.053
Chinese money laundry. Heh.

13:28.557 --> 13:29.891
How much in the case?

13:30.851 --> 13:33.561
Anywhere between 350 and half a mill.

13:38.734 --> 13:40.068
How much do you need, Val?

13:40.236 --> 13:43.238
Ah, we split it 50-50.

13:43.572 --> 13:46.825
I mean, how much do you need
to buy your way back?

13:51.247 --> 13:52.413
Into the syndicate.

13:53.749 --> 13:55.083
How much?

13:55.292 --> 13:57.001
- The Outfit?
- Whatever.

13:57.253 --> 13:59.671
Jesus. You know everything.

14:00.589 --> 14:02.423
Hi, sweetie.

14:02.591 --> 14:03.758
[CHUCKLES]

14:03.926 --> 14:05.426
130 grand.

14:13.936 --> 14:18.439
The Chows won't go to the cops.
They keep everything in-house.

14:18.649 --> 14:20.692
And they don't feel pain like we do.

14:20.985 --> 14:23.570
You notice anything about those guys?

14:23.779 --> 14:26.781
They look nasty.
Probably kung fu motherfuckers.

14:27.074 --> 14:30.785
- Did I miss something?
- They weren't wearing seat belts.

14:33.122 --> 14:35.123
We'll hit them on Friday.

14:50.806 --> 14:53.766
Hubba, hubba, hubba! Ahem.

14:55.936 --> 15:05.904
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

15:07.489 --> 15:08.823
[SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

15:34.475 --> 15:35.642
[GRUNTS]

15:36.977 --> 15:39.687
Lookie here. Unh.

15:39.855 --> 15:41.439
[MAN GRUNTING]

15:43.192 --> 15:45.068
[TIRES SCREECH]

15:46.445 --> 15:50.365
VAL:
Unh. How's that pileup taste, huh?

15:50.532 --> 15:52.492
[VAL GRUNTING]

15:53.827 --> 15:56.454
PORTER:
Daddy brought home the bacon, baby.

15:57.373 --> 15:59.040
[VAL GRUNTING]

16:02.836 --> 16:03.878
[HORN HONKS]

16:04.046 --> 16:06.714
- Val!
- What?

16:10.928 --> 16:13.221
[CHUCKLES]

16:17.226 --> 16:19.268
[LAUGHING]

16:19.770 --> 16:21.604
[PORTER SIGHS]

16:22.356 --> 16:24.107
Problem with kicking a Chow's ass...

16:24.316 --> 16:26.234
...is an hour later
you want to do it again.

16:26.402 --> 16:27.860
[CHUCKLES]

16:28.028 --> 16:30.154
Huh? Huh?

16:30.322 --> 16:31.990
Ah.

16:46.422 --> 16:47.588
140 grand.

16:48.424 --> 16:49.590
140 apiece.

16:50.426 --> 16:51.426
Total.

16:53.595 --> 16:54.595
Total?

16:58.767 --> 17:01.936
That's 70 grand?
That's not enough.

17:02.146 --> 17:06.023
Is for me.
I'm taking a few months off.

17:06.275 --> 17:10.694
I'm up short. Sixty short.
Fucking slants!

17:10.945 --> 17:12.780
Should have hit them Tuesday.

17:13.073 --> 17:14.615
Fuck!

17:15.659 --> 17:17.076
We got away clean.

17:18.244 --> 17:20.121
And got something to show for it.

17:20.789 --> 17:23.790
Be grateful for what you get,
rule number one.

17:27.463 --> 17:29.797
Yeah, rule number one.

17:39.058 --> 17:40.141
What?

17:47.441 --> 17:48.983
Everything's cool.

17:50.319 --> 17:52.570
Just not enough! All right?

17:52.863 --> 17:54.489
Never is, Val.

17:55.449 --> 17:58.409
Baby, just put the money
in the car, will you?

18:09.338 --> 18:13.257
I can't fucking believe it.
You know what, Porter?

18:15.219 --> 18:16.344
This is funny.

18:16.804 --> 18:18.429
This will kill you.

18:20.849 --> 18:22.850
It's always 140.

18:24.895 --> 18:26.437
[GUN COCKS]

18:28.899 --> 18:31.192
Someone ought to give me a Ph.D.
Ha, ha.

18:31.360 --> 18:32.485
[PORTER GROWLS]

18:34.863 --> 18:36.197
[GUN CLICKING]

18:36.365 --> 18:39.659
VAL: Jesus! Wait till I'm out
of the fucking way!

18:39.827 --> 18:41.619
[GASPING]

18:49.711 --> 18:52.964
Okay. Everything's cool, baby.

18:55.759 --> 18:57.301
Oh!

18:57.469 --> 18:59.554
[PORTER GRUNTING]

19:00.889 --> 19:06.060
Ah! You were great.
Everything's cool. Give me...

19:06.353 --> 19:08.229
Okay, keep the gun.

19:08.438 --> 19:12.900
That's it. Everything's cool.
It's just like we planned.

19:13.235 --> 19:16.863
Come on.
Don't fall apart on me now.

19:17.447 --> 19:19.323
There we go.

19:20.075 --> 19:22.827
[PANTING]

19:25.164 --> 19:27.081
[PORTER GRUNTING]

19:30.127 --> 19:33.713
Oh, I bet you got a lot of questions
rattling in your head, huh?

19:33.881 --> 19:36.215
[GASPING]

19:39.803 --> 19:41.762
Lynn did not understand.

19:43.265 --> 19:44.432
I don't know.

19:44.808 --> 19:48.269
Wives get funny
when it comes to girlfriends.

19:50.022 --> 19:51.105
[PORTER GASPING]

19:51.273 --> 19:52.273
What?

19:53.942 --> 19:55.443
I didn't get that.

19:56.820 --> 19:58.070
You got it.

19:59.740 --> 20:01.490
[GRUNTS]

20:09.291 --> 20:11.125
[DOOR CLOSES
THEN ENGINE STARTS]

20:12.127 --> 20:14.212
[TIRES SCREECHING]

20:14.379 --> 20:17.298
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

20:30.479 --> 20:33.731
Come on, Miss Porter.
I don't have all day.

20:45.577 --> 20:47.328
[SIGHS]

20:51.041 --> 20:53.000
[SNIFFS]

20:53.168 --> 20:56.128
Is, uh, Miss Porter here?

20:57.673 --> 20:58.756
Mrs. Porter.

21:02.719 --> 21:03.761
Yeah, whatever.

21:04.680 --> 21:07.515
[GRUNTS]

21:07.683 --> 21:09.475
Motherfucker!

21:10.936 --> 21:13.062
[COUGHING]

21:13.230 --> 21:15.231
Get up. Turn around.

21:15.691 --> 21:16.941
Come on.

21:21.488 --> 21:23.239
What have we got here? Huh?

21:25.867 --> 21:27.410
How much in here? Huh?

21:28.078 --> 21:29.120
Two grand.

21:29.371 --> 21:31.163
- What's in here?
- Helium.

21:31.498 --> 21:33.708
What do you think it is?
It's heroin.

21:33.875 --> 21:35.960
[GRUNTING]

21:36.128 --> 21:38.045
[GROANING]

21:42.384 --> 21:44.302
Shit. Oh, shit.

21:46.555 --> 21:48.264
Val Resnick.

21:48.932 --> 21:49.974
Where is he?

21:51.476 --> 21:54.145
You want to know where he is?
Ha, ha.

21:54.313 --> 21:55.479
He's right here.

21:55.897 --> 21:57.565
Look. Fuck you.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.191
Wrong answer.

22:00.068 --> 22:04.238
Aah! God! You motherfucker!

22:04.489 --> 22:06.907
- Fuck!
- Val Resnick.

22:08.368 --> 22:10.328
I never heard of him, man.

22:10.537 --> 22:12.163
Where'd you get the shit?

22:13.540 --> 22:16.917
Come on, man.
They're going to fucking kill me.

22:17.085 --> 22:18.336
[GUN COCKS]

22:21.423 --> 22:24.800
What do you think I'm
going to do? Worry about me.

22:25.886 --> 22:29.096
Oh, come on. Okay, okay.

22:29.514 --> 22:32.099
Stegman, man.
Arthur fucking Stegman, okay?

22:33.101 --> 22:34.560
Where is he?

22:36.271 --> 22:38.189
South End Taxi.

22:39.107 --> 22:40.858
Farragut Road, man.

22:43.820 --> 22:44.862
Thanks.

22:46.948 --> 22:48.532
You're welcome.

23:11.932 --> 23:13.599
I'm looking for Arthur Stegman.

23:14.976 --> 23:17.728
He ain't here.
Something I can help you with?

23:18.313 --> 23:20.815
No, you can't. Where is he?

23:21.566 --> 23:22.900
I don't know.

23:26.113 --> 23:27.113
Take a guess.

23:28.407 --> 23:29.407
What?

23:31.952 --> 23:34.078
Take a guess about where he is.

23:34.246 --> 23:35.663
[SCOFFS]

23:39.167 --> 23:40.668
[SIGHS]

23:44.089 --> 23:45.881
Is he at home?

23:49.761 --> 23:51.429
Go fuck yourself.

23:53.473 --> 23:54.974
[SIGHS]

23:55.142 --> 23:56.183
MAN 1:
Here we go.

23:56.435 --> 23:58.519
MAN 2: This one's mine.
MAN 1: Roll it.

23:58.770 --> 24:00.354
Wait, that was mine.

24:00.522 --> 24:03.691
[ALL CHATTERING]

24:08.029 --> 24:10.281
There's somebody here to see you.

24:13.952 --> 24:15.911
I'm looking for Stegman.

24:21.543 --> 24:23.169
Who the hell are you?

24:25.213 --> 24:26.464
I'm Porter.

24:27.549 --> 24:31.302
Porter, that looks like, uh, assault to me.

24:33.972 --> 24:37.183
Porter looks like he likes
to resist arrest.

24:40.312 --> 24:42.730
- Hey, hey! Whoa!
- Fuck! Not in here.

24:43.064 --> 24:45.065
Jesus! He just wants to talk.

24:45.484 --> 24:48.444
Am I right? Did I call it?

24:51.740 --> 24:52.865
Are you Stegman?

24:54.910 --> 24:57.411
Maybe. What do you want?

24:59.080 --> 25:01.207
Your boy didn't make his delivery.

25:02.709 --> 25:05.252
STEGMAN: Jesus.
- Whoa, Artie.

25:05.420 --> 25:07.963
Why don't we talk outside?

25:08.256 --> 25:09.298
You're a dealer?

25:10.675 --> 25:13.302
Just forget about it, all right?

25:13.512 --> 25:16.347
Don't touch my money either.
Come on...

25:16.598 --> 25:17.973
This is heroin?

25:19.768 --> 25:21.101
This is heroin.

25:21.853 --> 25:24.396
Don't worry about it.
Take it easy.

25:25.023 --> 25:26.106
Let's talk.

25:27.609 --> 25:30.069
What are you looking at?
Play your game.

25:31.029 --> 25:33.697
And you're bleeding
all over my couch!

25:33.949 --> 25:34.990
Come on!

25:40.580 --> 25:42.873
Steggie's been holding out on us.

25:44.125 --> 25:45.709
I'll check it out.

25:46.795 --> 25:48.504
PORTER:
Val Resnick.

25:50.799 --> 25:52.633
STEGMAN: What about him?
- Tell me where he is.

25:52.801 --> 25:55.761
Even if I knew,
the answer would still be no.

25:56.054 --> 25:59.223
- Where'd you meet up with my boy?
- At his drop.

25:59.391 --> 26:00.432
Is he dead?

26:00.725 --> 26:04.395
No, but she is. OD'd on that crap
you've been sending her.

26:04.646 --> 26:07.147
So? What do you care?

26:07.440 --> 26:09.149
I'm her husband.

26:10.652 --> 26:12.736
You're not going to kill me.
are you? Heh.

26:16.116 --> 26:17.658
Not in front of these kids.

26:19.828 --> 26:21.245
Where is he?

26:25.458 --> 26:26.458
I don't know!

26:27.627 --> 26:28.752
That's the truth.

26:29.004 --> 26:33.507
It got delivered to me last night.
I won't see anyone till next month.

26:33.675 --> 26:35.467
[STEGMAN SIGHS]

26:35.635 --> 26:37.303
Why all the trouble?

26:38.638 --> 26:41.056
He's afraid of the girl.
I mean...

26:41.474 --> 26:43.809
...of Mrs. Porter.

26:44.019 --> 26:47.104
I mean, that's how it looks to me.

26:54.696 --> 26:56.488
I don't know nothing about this.

26:56.823 --> 26:58.782
I know Val from the old days.

26:59.034 --> 27:01.660
Three months ago, he asks me
to do him a favor.

27:01.870 --> 27:05.456
I make an extra grand a month.
I figure, what the hell?

27:05.707 --> 27:10.377
Now you threaten to kill me?
That much a buddy of Val's I am not.

27:10.670 --> 27:13.631
He's in the city.
That's all I know.

27:13.882 --> 27:15.341
How do you know that?

27:16.509 --> 27:18.260
- He said so.
- When?

27:18.720 --> 27:22.681
When he came. Said he squared
himself with the syndicate.

27:22.891 --> 27:25.601
Said he was back
in the big time for good.

27:25.894 --> 27:27.227
He was very excited.

27:27.520 --> 27:30.481
You tell him that Porter is back too.

27:30.815 --> 27:33.108
And he wants his money.

27:33.360 --> 27:36.737
I'll come back for you
when these kids are not around.

27:39.991 --> 27:41.575
When would I tell him this?

27:56.633 --> 27:57.758
[DINGS]

28:01.262 --> 28:02.971
[RINGS]

28:03.139 --> 28:04.682
Talk to me. Ahem.

28:04.849 --> 28:08.519
[MAN ON PHONE]: There's a young lady
to see you. Her name is Pearl.

28:08.728 --> 28:10.729
She's got two very bad habits.

28:10.939 --> 28:13.649
Right now I'm only interested
in one of them.

28:13.817 --> 28:16.360
Ha, ha. Send her up.

28:19.197 --> 28:23.075
Apartment 718, ma'am.
Go right on up.

28:38.883 --> 28:40.801
[PHONE RINGS]

28:42.137 --> 28:43.345
Send her up.

28:43.638 --> 28:46.807
HASKELL: It's Haskell.
Sorry to call you at home...

28:47.058 --> 28:49.184
Don't be sorry.
Just don't call.

28:49.394 --> 28:52.479
I got a call from a cab guy
on the south end.

28:52.647 --> 28:53.981
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

28:54.149 --> 28:55.607
- What is it?
- It's this guy, Stegman.

28:55.900 --> 28:58.318
Shit. Hold on a second. Ahem.

29:04.492 --> 29:06.243
[VAL GRUNTS]

29:06.411 --> 29:10.497
On your knees, bitch.
I want satisfaction.

29:10.915 --> 29:12.875
- I'm on the phone, Pearl.
- Unh.

29:13.835 --> 29:15.669
[BOTH GRUNT]

29:16.671 --> 29:18.922
It's "Mistress Pearl."

29:19.174 --> 29:22.092
- I'm on the fucking phone!
- Unh!

29:22.260 --> 29:24.136
[PEARL GIGGLES]

29:24.304 --> 29:27.181
Ahem. Make it quick, huh?

29:27.849 --> 29:29.725
This guy Stegman calls.

29:30.018 --> 29:34.354
He sounded all nervous,
like something scared him.

29:34.606 --> 29:38.317
He had to talk to you.
I said I'd see what I could do.

29:38.860 --> 29:42.613
- What was it about?
- He said to tell you Lynn was dead.

29:43.198 --> 29:47.951
He said some guy wanted you.
That's all he said.

29:48.203 --> 29:49.828
I thought you ought to know.

29:50.705 --> 29:53.207
You did right.
I want to talk to him. Ahem.

29:53.500 --> 29:55.000
Who, Stegman?

29:55.710 --> 29:58.670
No, President Nixon.
Of course, Stegman!

29:59.005 --> 30:01.340
Tell him, uh, Varrick's, by the bridge.

30:01.633 --> 30:04.551
Make it, uh... Hmm.

30:04.719 --> 30:06.512
Make it 20 minutes.

30:06.679 --> 30:09.306
- Hmm.
- I'm working here!

30:15.313 --> 30:18.565
- Unh!
- Can't you see I'm working here?

30:18.733 --> 30:20.192
[VAL GROANS]

30:22.654 --> 30:23.946
Put it on my tab.

30:24.197 --> 30:26.114
PORTER:
I'm looking for a girl.

30:26.908 --> 30:31.078
She goes by the name of Rosie.
Here's her photo. Do you know her?

30:33.998 --> 30:36.708
She worked by telephone,
not freelance.

30:37.418 --> 30:39.628
Probably connected
with the syndicate.

30:39.838 --> 30:42.965
Out of my league.
I wouldn't know her.

30:45.385 --> 30:47.594
Maybe you know somebody who would.

30:53.518 --> 30:56.353
- Why you looking for her?
- I'm her brother.

30:56.604 --> 30:59.273
I got cancer.
I want to see her.

31:05.780 --> 31:07.364
You two look close.

31:10.285 --> 31:11.994
Got a cigarette?

31:17.458 --> 31:19.877
Your sister sounds expensive.

31:20.295 --> 31:24.047
Try Michael,
bartender at the Regal Hotel.

31:24.924 --> 31:27.092
That wasn't the name
I was looking for.

31:28.553 --> 31:30.762
The only one I got.

31:57.332 --> 31:58.749
[CHUCKLES]

31:58.917 --> 32:03.003
I tried to call you, but you
must have changed your number.

32:03.254 --> 32:06.214
- I never gave you my original number.
- Ha, ha.

32:07.842 --> 32:09.509
What did this guy look like?

32:10.261 --> 32:12.429
He had dark hair, blue eyes.

32:12.639 --> 32:15.390
A real Cro-Magnon-looking bastard.

32:15.600 --> 32:17.684
If Lynn's dead,
maybe he did us a favor.

32:17.852 --> 32:21.313
Ha, ha. I know, except I'm out
a grand a month.

32:21.606 --> 32:23.982
Maybe we can work something out. Ahem.

32:24.150 --> 32:26.318
- Did you get a name?
- Mm.

32:26.486 --> 32:28.070
He said he was Porter.

32:29.781 --> 32:31.865
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

32:32.033 --> 32:33.867
He said he was there for Porter?

32:34.535 --> 32:36.495
No, he said he was Porter.

32:42.543 --> 32:45.629
I wouldn't want that guy
after me either.

32:45.880 --> 32:49.508
- I know how you must feel.
- What am I? A nobody?

32:50.718 --> 32:53.720
I've got friends.
All I have to do is point.

32:54.055 --> 32:56.306
I pick up a phone
and he's a dead man.

32:56.724 --> 32:58.350
And this time he stays dead!

32:58.893 --> 33:01.436
Try to keep it down,
all right?

33:01.896 --> 33:03.480
It's okay.

33:04.148 --> 33:05.440
What'd he say about me?

33:06.067 --> 33:08.151
He said you owed him money.

33:08.903 --> 33:09.945
Nothing else?

33:10.405 --> 33:12.781
Nothing. Why?
How much you owe him?

33:13.574 --> 33:14.950
None of your business.

33:16.202 --> 33:19.496
I just got the feeling
he'd like to kill you.

33:20.164 --> 33:21.790
Oh, Christ!

33:22.583 --> 33:23.875
Porter.

33:28.923 --> 33:30.549
What?

33:30.800 --> 33:31.842
What'd you tell him?

33:32.510 --> 33:33.593
Nothing!

33:33.928 --> 33:37.764
- What could I tell him?
- You tell him about the money? Heroin?

33:37.932 --> 33:40.934
He had it with him!
I told him I delivered it.

33:41.185 --> 33:42.477
Nothing else?

33:42.770 --> 33:44.521
I don't know nothing else!

33:44.939 --> 33:49.568
You gave him something. A name.
Someone who knows where to find me.

33:49.861 --> 33:52.029
I swear on my mother...

33:52.238 --> 33:53.405
Fuck your mother!

33:54.449 --> 33:58.326
- That's not nice. Take it easy.
- What are you looking at?

33:58.870 --> 34:01.455
STEGMAN: Val, don't.
Not again. Don't do that, man.

34:01.622 --> 34:03.957
- What the fuck you looking at?
- No, Val, don't.

34:04.125 --> 34:05.751
Come on. Not again.

34:05.960 --> 34:07.044
Don't.

34:07.295 --> 34:10.005
- Forget it.
MANAGER: Is there some trouble here?

34:10.297 --> 34:12.841
We're just leaving.

34:13.967 --> 34:16.344
You know what?
This one's on me.

34:16.637 --> 34:19.306
You see me reaching
for my fucking wallet?

34:23.101 --> 34:27.731
Sorry. He just got a promotion,
so he's a little tense.

34:29.567 --> 34:31.234
Is there a Michael here?

34:31.444 --> 34:33.360
That's him over yonder.

34:35.656 --> 34:37.074
PORTER:
Michael.

34:37.492 --> 34:40.659
You're the man to see
about horizontal refreshment?

34:40.995 --> 34:43.705
I'm looking for a girl named Rosie.

34:43.915 --> 34:47.793
Prostitution is illegal
and you're speaking Greek.

34:51.422 --> 34:55.300
Usually these matters are conducted
with more discretion.

34:58.096 --> 34:59.429
[SCREAMS]

34:59.597 --> 35:00.597
Be discreet now.

35:02.642 --> 35:04.142
[COUGHS]

35:06.687 --> 35:08.688
- What was her name?
- Rosie.

35:08.940 --> 35:11.525
- Who's looking for her?
- Just call her.

35:19.700 --> 35:21.201
[LINE RINGING]

35:21.369 --> 35:22.494
- Rosie?
ROSIE: Yeah?

35:22.662 --> 35:24.329
PORTER:
Give me the phone.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.916
- Unh!
- Take care of that.

35:29.752 --> 35:32.254
- Rosie.
- Who the hell is this?

35:32.463 --> 35:33.672
- Porter.
- Ha, ha.

35:33.840 --> 35:36.383
Try again, honey.
Porter's dead.

35:37.009 --> 35:41.304
I used to drive for you.
Provide a safe work environment.

35:41.722 --> 35:42.764
Porter?

35:44.308 --> 35:45.517
Yeah.

35:56.696 --> 35:59.781
PORTER:
Why pour salt on old wounds?

36:00.575 --> 36:02.450
I didn't need to.

36:05.037 --> 36:07.873
I guess I had a soft spot for her.

36:18.593 --> 36:21.344
[ROSIE LAUGHING]

36:31.564 --> 36:32.647
Come in.

36:34.442 --> 36:36.860
You look pretty good
for a dead guy.

36:43.034 --> 36:44.784
How'd you hear about it?

36:45.536 --> 36:46.912
People were talking.

36:47.205 --> 36:49.664
Plus I heard your wife
was back in town alone.

36:49.832 --> 36:51.750
[PORTER SIGHS]

36:51.918 --> 36:53.543
She's dead.

36:54.629 --> 36:56.671
I'm sorry, Porter.

36:57.632 --> 36:58.798
Why?

37:00.092 --> 37:04.596
Jesus. Surly Porter.
You're the same as ever, aren't you?

37:08.142 --> 37:10.227
This doesn't look like you.

37:11.562 --> 37:13.063
Yeah, well, people change.

37:13.231 --> 37:14.522
[DOG GROWLING]

37:14.690 --> 37:15.982
ROSIE:
Stay.

37:16.317 --> 37:18.777
It's okay.
Come on, sweetheart.

37:19.820 --> 37:22.280
Meet the nastiest dog
who ever lived.

37:25.326 --> 37:26.451
What's his name?

37:27.286 --> 37:28.328
Porter.

37:29.956 --> 37:31.915
He took your job after you left.

37:32.166 --> 37:35.252
He's just as tough,
but he won't leave me. Mwah.

37:44.178 --> 37:45.387
I need a favor.

37:46.931 --> 37:48.306
A favor?

37:48.683 --> 37:51.142
Maybe you're not the same as ever.

37:54.230 --> 37:56.356
I'm looking for a syndicate boy.

37:58.109 --> 38:00.527
It's the Outfit.
We don't say "syndicate" anymore.

38:00.736 --> 38:02.529
You know what I mean.
Whatever.

38:02.738 --> 38:05.282
Don't get touchy, Porter.
What's his name?

38:07.702 --> 38:09.035
Val Resnick.

38:12.039 --> 38:13.373
That son of a bitch.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.167
You know him?

38:17.295 --> 38:21.339
I met up with him once
a few years ago.

38:21.716 --> 38:24.968
He can't use Star's service.
He beats up the girls.

38:25.219 --> 38:26.928
He almost killed one.

38:27.596 --> 38:28.638
You?

38:33.352 --> 38:36.646
Does it matter?
You quit looking after me, remember?

38:42.028 --> 38:44.154
Would you know where he might be?

38:46.866 --> 38:48.742
I suppose he's at the hotel.

38:49.577 --> 38:52.620
- Which one?
- The Outfit hotel.

38:53.622 --> 38:54.706
The address?

38:54.874 --> 38:56.458
[CHUCKLES]

38:57.335 --> 38:59.294
We're friends, right?

39:00.046 --> 39:03.923
I mean, we used to be.
But I'm an employee too.

39:04.216 --> 39:07.886
The Outfit wouldn't like me
telling you, would they?

39:08.596 --> 39:09.888
How strong are you?

39:10.097 --> 39:14.017
Personally, I think you are
the strongest man I've ever met.

39:14.268 --> 39:16.144
But I wonder if it's enough.

39:16.896 --> 39:18.271
For what?

39:19.023 --> 39:22.025
You want this guy
for something he won't like.

39:22.943 --> 39:24.152
I'm going to kill him.

39:27.698 --> 39:29.741
That's something he won't like.

39:32.203 --> 39:35.955
What if they grab you and ask you
how you found out?

39:36.207 --> 39:39.167
You know I wouldn't turn you in.

39:39.460 --> 39:42.295
- I wouldn't talk.
- What if they ask you hard?

39:44.131 --> 39:47.384
I'll say it was
a cab dispatcher named Stegman.

39:51.889 --> 39:54.432
The Oakwood Arms, Union and 17th.

40:19.166 --> 40:20.959
[VAL GRUNTS]

40:26.215 --> 40:27.257
Hi, Val.

40:30.010 --> 40:32.095
Where's my money?

40:32.638 --> 40:34.013
[VAL & PEARL GRUNT]

40:34.181 --> 40:37.475
[DEAN MARTIN'S "AIN'T THAT
A KICK IN THE HEAD" PLAYING ON RADIO]

40:37.643 --> 40:39.185
I took your gun.

40:39.437 --> 40:42.105
It's back here.
You look like a pro.

40:42.356 --> 40:45.483
Keep your mouth shut
and you'll walk out of here.

40:48.988 --> 40:51.197
My 70 grand. I want it.

40:51.365 --> 40:55.368
Uh, I don't have it right now.

40:55.870 --> 41:00.582
- Where is it?
- I gave all 130,000 to the Outfit.

41:00.875 --> 41:02.417
I gave it all to them.

41:04.545 --> 41:08.882
Tell them you gave them money that
doesn't belong to you. Get it back.

41:09.550 --> 41:12.594
I can't do that.
You don't know these...

41:14.305 --> 41:16.639
You'll kill me
whether I get it or not.

41:16.807 --> 41:18.141
[GUN COCKS]

41:18.309 --> 41:20.477
All right, I'll get the money.

41:20.728 --> 41:23.897
Just give me a few days.
What the fuck are you doing?

41:25.149 --> 41:26.983
Noon. Tomorrow.

41:27.151 --> 41:28.193
Say it.

41:28.819 --> 41:30.278
All right.

41:30.988 --> 41:33.656
This may sound crazy,
but, uh, no hard feelings, huh?

41:34.575 --> 41:37.744
I did what I had to do.
You can appreciate that.

41:38.037 --> 41:39.412
I appreciate that, you...

41:39.747 --> 41:40.955
No, no! Don't.

41:43.000 --> 41:44.042
Please.

41:44.335 --> 41:45.793
Allow me.

41:52.885 --> 41:55.011
VAL: Aah! Jesus!
- Ha-ha-ha!

41:57.598 --> 41:59.182
[VAL GRUNTS]

42:00.601 --> 42:02.435
[GRUNTS]

42:04.104 --> 42:05.396
VAL:
You bitch!

42:05.564 --> 42:06.731
[GUN COCKS]

42:08.025 --> 42:09.025
Let her work.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.949
[VAL GRUNTS]

42:16.116 --> 42:17.784
[VAL GROANS]

42:19.537 --> 42:21.955
[GRUNTING]

42:23.123 --> 42:24.499
Me love you, baby.

42:26.752 --> 42:29.087
- Me love you long time.
VAL: Aah!

42:29.255 --> 42:31.631
- Unh!
PEARL: Ha-ha-ha.

42:31.799 --> 42:34.133
[VAL COUGHING]

42:35.553 --> 42:36.970
No, no, wait.

42:37.137 --> 42:39.806
[VAL GRUNTING]

42:41.433 --> 42:42.892
[VAL PANTING]

42:43.060 --> 42:44.143
PORTER:
Tomorrow.

42:44.812 --> 42:45.937
Noon.

42:46.146 --> 42:50.483
You and the money be at 7th
and Franklin at the pay phone.

42:51.652 --> 42:54.654
Okay. Okay.

42:56.407 --> 42:57.949
Where'd you get this?

42:59.410 --> 43:01.869
Some hooker had it.
I recognized you.

43:02.162 --> 43:04.581
I swiped it in case I could use it.

43:04.832 --> 43:07.250
- Did you hurt her?
- Huh?

43:07.418 --> 43:09.419
The hooker.
Did you hurt her?

43:09.670 --> 43:11.504
What's that have to do
with anything?

43:13.132 --> 43:15.008
[GRUNTS]

43:20.806 --> 43:22.765
I've got a few minutes.

43:23.851 --> 43:25.852
So go boil an egg.

43:28.355 --> 43:30.523
[GRUNTS]

43:32.693 --> 43:36.446
Phillip says you have a problem
you need help with.

43:37.281 --> 43:38.323
VAL:
Yes, sir.

43:39.199 --> 43:40.533
Is it your problem...

43:40.701 --> 43:42.994
...who breached our security
last night?

43:43.162 --> 43:44.537
Yes, sir. Ahem.

43:44.705 --> 43:46.289
He breaks into my apartment...

43:46.498 --> 43:49.542
There's an old expression
that has served me well:

43:50.628 --> 43:53.004
"Do not shit where you eat."

43:54.965 --> 43:56.507
Or "live."

43:56.800 --> 43:58.259
"Do not shit where you live."

43:58.510 --> 43:59.802
I like that better.

44:00.554 --> 44:01.763
I'm sorry, Mr. Carter.

44:02.014 --> 44:04.474
There are three ways
we can handle this.

44:04.808 --> 44:09.312
One: We help you.
Two: We allow you to help yourself.

44:10.397 --> 44:12.774
Three: We have you replaced.

44:17.988 --> 44:22.909
We have an investment in you, Resnick,
of time, money and training.

44:23.327 --> 44:25.286
So assisting you would be...

44:25.496 --> 44:28.748
...in a way, protecting our investment.

44:29.166 --> 44:32.377
And that is always
good business policy.

44:32.670 --> 44:34.170
Yes, sir, Mr. Carter.

44:34.421 --> 44:36.422
Thank you.
You won't regret it.

44:40.928 --> 44:44.222
According to Phillip,
a man has come to town to kill you?

44:44.390 --> 44:45.431
Yes, sir.

44:45.599 --> 44:49.560
You say he's alone and that, uh,
he's a professional robber. Correct?

44:49.770 --> 44:52.855
Yes, sir. He does, uh, payroll jobs,
banks, stuff like that.

44:53.023 --> 44:54.649
CARTER:
Hmm.

44:54.817 --> 44:57.402
- What's his name?
- Porter.

44:58.237 --> 44:59.529
What's his first name?

45:05.703 --> 45:09.664
Uh, I don't know. He never called
himself anything but Porter. Ha, ha.

45:11.917 --> 45:13.251
Oh.

45:21.385 --> 45:24.762
Where did you get the $130,000?

45:29.476 --> 45:32.270
That's why this man
has come to town, huh?

45:32.813 --> 45:34.981
The $130,000 you paid us back.

45:35.149 --> 45:38.359
Uh, yes, sir.
But only $70,000 of it was his.

45:39.069 --> 45:43.656
We never asked you where you got it.
It's none of our business.

45:43.907 --> 45:47.118
Now it appears
it has become our business.

45:47.286 --> 45:48.995
[PHIL CLEARS THROAT]

45:50.414 --> 45:52.665
PHIL:
Here's his file, Mr. Carter.

46:00.090 --> 46:04.135
Do you understand your value
to the organization?

46:06.430 --> 46:10.391
You're a sadist, you lack compunction.
That comes in handy.

46:12.019 --> 46:16.939
But now, an area of your personal life
has become a danger to us.

46:19.985 --> 46:24.447
A man in our organization needs
to be tough, self-reliant.

46:25.365 --> 46:28.826
Were you to handle this problem
on your own...

46:30.412 --> 46:32.914
...there would be no doubt...

46:34.208 --> 46:36.083
...you're the kind of man we want.

46:36.293 --> 46:37.418
I want to. Ahem.

46:37.836 --> 46:40.171
I want to handle it myself.

46:40.380 --> 46:41.422
Great.

46:42.216 --> 46:46.469
Until it is handled, I want you
to move out of the Oakwood Arms.

46:48.055 --> 46:50.681
Uh, ahem, but I don't have a place, uh...

46:50.974 --> 46:54.352
I don't want any more
unpleasantness at the hotel.

46:55.562 --> 46:56.771
Yes, sir.

47:02.903 --> 47:05.780
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

47:05.948 --> 47:10.368
Excuse me, but it might be easier
if Resnick just disappeared.

47:11.995 --> 47:13.788
I thought about that.

47:14.414 --> 47:16.791
But I'm not worried about Resnick.

47:17.042 --> 47:20.127
He wouldn't last two minutes
on the street without us.

47:20.379 --> 47:22.755
It's that other mutt
I'm thinking about.

47:23.006 --> 47:24.549
- What's his name?
- Porter.

47:26.927 --> 47:31.722
Takes a lot of moxie to walk into
the Outfit and whack our guys around.

47:32.683 --> 47:34.433
Either that or he's shit nuts.

47:35.853 --> 47:38.980
Frankly, I don't understand it
for $130,000.

47:39.398 --> 47:41.357
It was $70,000, his share.

47:42.693 --> 47:44.360
That's even worse.

47:44.945 --> 47:47.822
I don't want
Mr. Bronson hearing about this.

47:48.282 --> 47:50.408
He'll think I'm getting soft.

47:50.742 --> 47:52.493
His principle has always been:

47:52.744 --> 47:55.705
"If you don't understand it,
get rid of it."

47:56.874 --> 48:00.084
A stitch in time, so to speak.

48:01.128 --> 48:02.962
Stitch this mutt up, Phil.

48:08.302 --> 48:10.511
Any Polaroids or trophies?

48:10.804 --> 48:12.388
No, not this time.

48:12.556 --> 48:13.639
[PHONE RINGING]

48:13.807 --> 48:15.391
MAN: Aah!
- Yeah?

48:15.893 --> 48:19.270
They cut me loose, Pearl,
like I thought they would.

48:19.646 --> 48:21.397
Hold on one second.

48:21.773 --> 48:25.818
Shut up!
I'm on the fucking phone!

48:25.986 --> 48:29.155
[WHIP SNAPPING THEN
MAN GRUNTING ON PHONE]

48:29.323 --> 48:30.740
[MAN WHIMPERING]

48:30.908 --> 48:32.450
[PEARL SIGHS]

48:35.787 --> 48:36.829
Yes?

48:37.497 --> 48:39.957
- Did your friends make it to town?
- Oh, yeah.

48:40.751 --> 48:42.001
Last night, baby.

48:42.169 --> 48:45.421
Did you tell them
Porter took their payroll?

48:45.672 --> 48:46.797
I did.

48:47.466 --> 48:49.383
And they want retribution.

48:49.968 --> 48:52.303
All right. Here's what we do.

49:18.121 --> 49:19.872
[TIRES SCREECHING]

49:24.544 --> 49:26.671
[GRUNTING]

49:29.675 --> 49:31.759
[GROANING]

49:54.074 --> 49:57.827
PEARL: Yeah, that's Porter.
He has shit for brains.

49:57.995 --> 49:59.704
Oh. Shit.

49:59.871 --> 50:01.247
[GROANING]

50:04.042 --> 50:06.210
[GRUNTING]

50:19.099 --> 50:22.601
[SIREN WAILS]

50:25.689 --> 50:26.981
Shit!

50:31.278 --> 50:32.862
CHOW THUG:
Next time, Porter.

50:33.030 --> 50:35.281
[PEARL SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

50:36.950 --> 50:39.118
Porter's made some new friends.

50:41.079 --> 50:42.246
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

50:42.414 --> 50:44.915
[COUGHS THEN GRUNTS]

50:50.255 --> 50:52.965
[COUGHING]

50:56.720 --> 50:58.304
]PORTER SIGHS]

50:59.264 --> 51:01.849
- Easy, mister.
- I won't press charges.

51:02.100 --> 51:04.143
- Who were they?
- I don't know.

51:04.311 --> 51:06.979
I'm all right. I don't want...
It's you guys.

51:07.230 --> 51:09.982
Stegman says you got
a line on a load of cash.

51:10.233 --> 51:12.568
250 grand, to be exact.

51:13.320 --> 51:14.403
Seventy.

51:14.571 --> 51:15.988
[PORTER GRUNTS]

51:16.156 --> 51:18.157
Come on, man, get off of me!

51:18.658 --> 51:21.494
What do you take us for, huh?
Idiots?

51:21.953 --> 51:24.580
Nobody'd go through all this
for 70 grand.

51:24.831 --> 51:27.541
You look like a whole bunch
of trouble to us.

51:27.834 --> 51:29.919
We found a dead girl full of heroin.

51:30.128 --> 51:33.672
There were signs of a struggle.
We're not sure it was an OD.

51:33.965 --> 51:36.509
We got a witness.
A guy with one nostril.

51:36.760 --> 51:38.844
- Remember him?
- Ah.

51:39.012 --> 51:41.514
Don't worry.
We'll give you immunity.

51:41.765 --> 51:44.058
Room to operate,
get-out-of-jail-free card.

51:44.351 --> 51:46.477
All you got to do is get the money.

51:46.645 --> 51:49.271
Oh. We can't help you, though.

51:50.023 --> 51:52.566
- It would be against the law.
- Understand?

51:54.986 --> 51:56.779
- It's my money.
HICKS: Wrong.

51:56.947 --> 51:58.656
[GRUNTS]

51:59.449 --> 52:00.783
It's our money.

52:01.034 --> 52:04.328
Me and my partner.
You be a good boy, we give you a piece.

52:04.538 --> 52:06.163
It'll be easy, Porter.

52:06.331 --> 52:08.040
- Unh!
- You got it?

52:08.708 --> 52:10.668
LEARY: He's got it.
- Understand?

52:12.003 --> 52:14.755
- Take it easy. We'll be in touch.
- Thanks.

52:15.132 --> 52:16.549
HICKS:
What a dope!

52:17.217 --> 52:18.342
Fuck.

52:18.635 --> 52:20.511
PORTER:
Crooked cops.

52:20.846 --> 52:23.055
Do they come any other way?

52:24.141 --> 52:29.061
If I'd been just a little dumber,
I could've joined the force myself.

53:00.218 --> 53:03.512
Jesus Christ, Porter,
you need to see a doctor.

53:04.764 --> 53:08.100
- It's going to sting.
- Just clean it up, all right?

53:09.019 --> 53:11.020
- You hold it there.
- Yeah, all right.

53:23.617 --> 53:25.242
I'll do it.

53:30.874 --> 53:32.958
Tell me something, Porter.

53:35.212 --> 53:39.256
When did you decide to leave?
That night we slept together?

53:40.759 --> 53:41.842
No.

53:42.969 --> 53:44.011
[SIGHS]

53:44.179 --> 53:46.597
The next day,
when I drove you to work.

53:52.145 --> 53:53.687
Should've asked me to quit.

53:58.902 --> 54:01.946
You could've asked me
to drive you somewhere else.

54:09.329 --> 54:11.163
[SIGHS]

54:15.835 --> 54:18.128
Hubba, hubba, hubba. Ha, ha.

54:25.804 --> 54:26.845
Thanks.

54:27.806 --> 54:30.641
- Does it fit?
- Oh, yeah.

54:31.309 --> 54:32.977
Like it was made for me.

54:34.437 --> 54:36.230
It'll look great in your casket.

54:47.701 --> 54:49.451
You know what I think?

54:49.869 --> 54:54.248
I think that, uh, all those stories
about you being dead were true.

54:54.457 --> 54:57.167
You're too thickheaded to admit it.

55:26.406 --> 55:28.157
ROSIE:
God, I missed you.

55:28.408 --> 55:30.242
I miss you.

55:35.665 --> 55:38.042
[ROSIE GRUNTS]

55:38.668 --> 55:40.252
Don't, don't, don't...

55:42.005 --> 55:43.839
I can't. I got, uh...

55:46.426 --> 55:48.218
...stuff to do.

55:50.930 --> 55:52.931
[PORTER SIGHS]

55:54.559 --> 55:55.893
[CLEARS THROAT]

56:06.237 --> 56:07.613
[DOOR CLOSES]

56:29.260 --> 56:31.470
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

56:31.638 --> 56:33.138
ROSIE:
Porter.

56:34.099 --> 56:35.641
[GUN COCKS]

56:40.480 --> 56:42.064
[WHISPERING]
Where is he?

56:45.610 --> 56:47.945
Porter. Where is he?

56:48.238 --> 56:49.988
[WHISPERING]
He's in the bedroom.

56:53.159 --> 56:54.868
[ROSIE GRUNTS]

57:05.422 --> 57:07.297
Is he hurt bad?

57:08.925 --> 57:11.176
The doctor should be here any minute.

57:11.428 --> 57:13.554
That's bullshit.

57:26.151 --> 57:27.317
[ROSIE GRUNTS]

57:27.485 --> 57:30.571
Porter. Here I come, pally.

57:30.738 --> 57:32.239
[DOG BARKING]

57:32.407 --> 57:33.866
ROSIE:
Porter!

57:34.033 --> 57:35.868
VAL:
Goddamn!

57:36.035 --> 57:37.202
[GUNSHOT]

57:37.370 --> 57:38.537
ROSIE:
Goddamn!

57:40.665 --> 57:43.083
[BOTH GRUNTING]

57:43.251 --> 57:45.085
VAL:
Whoa!

57:46.129 --> 57:47.629
- Get in here!
- Aah!

57:49.674 --> 57:51.633
Ah.

57:51.801 --> 57:53.969
[ROSIE GROANING]

57:54.137 --> 57:55.220
Where is he?

57:55.472 --> 57:57.681
He's gone, he's gone.

57:58.308 --> 57:59.808
Gone, huh?

58:03.229 --> 58:06.064
I know you.
You're that whore from the picture.

58:08.234 --> 58:09.776
[CHUCKLES]

58:09.944 --> 58:11.653
How do you know him?

58:12.238 --> 58:13.822
He used to drive me.

58:16.034 --> 58:18.494
[CHOKING]

58:18.661 --> 58:20.454
I'm driving you now, honey.

58:20.622 --> 58:22.247
[ROSIE LAUGHS]

58:22.415 --> 58:24.041
You know what you are?

58:24.250 --> 58:25.751
Educate me.

58:26.169 --> 58:28.212
An ugly pig who beats up women...

58:28.421 --> 58:32.424
...who can't get it up because
he's terrified of his own shadow!

58:32.675 --> 58:33.759
- Is that right?
- Yup.

58:34.052 --> 58:35.260
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

58:35.428 --> 58:37.804
- Then you must be the lucky girl.
- Aah!

58:40.058 --> 58:44.186
Oh! Hubba, hubba, hubba!
I knew I'd seen that ass before.

58:46.439 --> 58:49.107
I am going to fuck you
six ways from Sunday.

59:04.749 --> 59:06.124
[VAL GRUNTING]

59:07.961 --> 59:09.378
[SCREAMS]

59:14.968 --> 59:17.469
[VAL GRUNTING]

59:18.805 --> 59:20.597
I forgot my cigarettes.

59:24.811 --> 59:26.979
[VAL GRUNTING]

59:31.317 --> 59:32.985
All right, Val.

59:33.903 --> 59:38.407
This Outfit, or whatever you call it,
it's got a head man, right?

59:38.741 --> 59:40.325
Who is it?

59:40.743 --> 59:42.119
They'll kill me.

59:42.620 --> 59:44.413
What do you think I'll do?
Worry about me.

59:44.581 --> 59:46.456
Oh! God damn!

59:47.417 --> 59:48.959
Names. Come on.

59:49.961 --> 59:53.130
Fairfax and Carter.
They run the whole city.

59:55.133 --> 59:56.842
PORTER:
Where do I find them?

59:57.343 --> 59:59.177
Fairfax isn't in town.

59:59.971 --> 01:00:01.972
What about Carter?
Is he in town?

01:00:04.017 --> 01:00:06.518
Porter, it won't do you any good.

01:00:06.853 --> 01:00:09.187
They're going to...
Jesus!

01:00:10.857 --> 01:00:14.901
Frederick Carter Investments.
120 Commerce Avenue.

01:00:15.069 --> 01:00:17.696
- Oh. Oh.
- Thanks.

01:00:20.658 --> 01:00:21.950
All right!

01:00:22.827 --> 01:00:25.871
All right!
I'll help you out.

01:00:27.206 --> 01:00:31.209
You're fucking nuts going up
against the Outfit for 70 grand.

01:00:31.461 --> 01:00:33.670
But I'm going to help you out.

01:00:34.464 --> 01:00:35.756
Here. Keep talking.

01:00:38.676 --> 01:00:40.552
Thanks. I...

01:00:42.138 --> 01:00:45.182
I can get you in.
It's tighter than a drum.

01:00:45.350 --> 01:00:46.391
How many guys?

01:00:46.559 --> 01:00:47.643
[GRUNTS]

01:00:47.810 --> 01:00:49.227
It's tighter than hell.

01:00:49.479 --> 01:00:53.565
Only one guy on the outside.
So I got a way around that.

01:00:53.733 --> 01:00:56.735
[LAUGHING]

01:00:56.903 --> 01:00:58.570
You are crazy!

01:00:58.821 --> 01:01:00.697
You're a crazy son of a bitch!

01:01:01.574 --> 01:01:03.408
That's why I love you.

01:01:04.035 --> 01:01:05.327
You got a light?

01:01:05.495 --> 01:01:06.912
I, uh... Huh?

01:01:07.080 --> 01:01:08.872
- You got a light?
- Uh...

01:01:12.085 --> 01:01:14.461
- No.
- Then what good are you?

01:01:14.754 --> 01:01:16.213
VAL:
Check my pocket!

01:01:16.381 --> 01:01:17.839
[GUNSHOT]

01:01:22.053 --> 01:01:23.679
[SIGHS]

01:01:39.028 --> 01:01:42.614
Rosie. Rosie.

01:01:44.367 --> 01:01:45.826
Is your name on the lease?

01:01:51.124 --> 01:01:53.542
The Outfit pays for everything.

01:01:54.961 --> 01:01:57.921
I want you to gather
everything up that you need.

01:01:58.297 --> 01:02:00.298
Say goodbye to this place.

01:02:18.901 --> 01:02:21.278
[DOG WHIMPERING]

01:02:25.116 --> 01:02:26.324
ROSIE:
It's okay, baby.

01:02:26.743 --> 01:02:28.243
It's okay, puppy.

01:02:28.745 --> 01:02:30.537
He'll live. How are you?

01:02:38.171 --> 01:02:39.588
Yeah, I know.

01:02:39.839 --> 01:02:42.466
It's not much,
but at least you'll be safe.

01:02:42.675 --> 01:02:44.801
Nobody knows I'm here.
Sit down. Relax.

01:02:44.969 --> 01:02:46.595
[PHONE RINGING]

01:03:00.693 --> 01:03:01.818
What?

01:03:03.529 --> 01:03:05.614
Nobody has this number.

01:03:05.782 --> 01:03:25.050
[RINGING CONTINUES]

01:03:25.218 --> 01:03:27.260
[DOG WHIMPERS]

01:03:35.061 --> 01:03:36.394
What?

01:03:36.562 --> 01:03:38.647
[RINGING CONTINUES]

01:03:49.534 --> 01:03:52.077
Somebody does know I'm here.

01:03:52.745 --> 01:03:54.871
[LINE RINGING]

01:03:55.039 --> 01:03:56.581
[SIGHS]

01:03:56.749 --> 01:03:58.834
He's probably fucking her.

01:03:59.085 --> 01:04:02.921
- He's taking long enough.
- Maybe the dog too.

01:04:03.422 --> 01:04:05.131
You think so?

01:04:06.384 --> 01:04:07.968
Give it a minute.

01:04:34.954 --> 01:04:37.998
Okay, let's give him another bell.

01:04:41.377 --> 01:04:43.587
[DIALING PHONE]

01:04:46.549 --> 01:04:47.966
Shit.

01:04:48.801 --> 01:04:51.094
He's behind us.

01:05:09.071 --> 01:05:11.072
[ALL SCREAMING]

01:05:24.086 --> 01:05:26.254
PORTER:
It's not just anybody that gets...

01:05:26.464 --> 01:05:29.633
...a hit put on him by a big firm
like the Outfit.

01:05:30.009 --> 01:05:32.177
I was moving up in the world.

01:05:33.846 --> 01:05:36.556
Maybe it was time
to pay them a visit.

01:05:36.849 --> 01:05:39.309
Carter wouldn't be expecting that.

01:05:40.019 --> 01:05:43.271
And who knows?
I might even get my money back.

01:05:43.606 --> 01:05:46.441
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:06:13.719 --> 01:06:15.011
HICKS:
I told you he'd show.

01:06:15.221 --> 01:06:16.846
Give me my goddamn money, please.

01:06:17.014 --> 01:06:19.224
[ALL ARGUING INDISTINCTLY]

01:06:19.392 --> 01:06:21.768
HICKS: Give me my money.
LEARY: You sure that's him?

01:06:22.019 --> 01:06:23.061
STEGMAN:
Yeah, come on.

01:06:24.855 --> 01:06:26.815
Thank you very much.

01:06:28.859 --> 01:06:30.068
What you up to, buddy?

01:06:30.236 --> 01:06:32.696
Ah. Well, our money's in there...

01:06:33.406 --> 01:06:35.407
...if you're still interested.

01:06:35.616 --> 01:06:38.368
Not in the dough,
but, uh, the boat I'll buy with it.

01:06:38.536 --> 01:06:39.703
[CHUCKLING]

01:06:42.206 --> 01:06:44.165
What's he doing here?

01:06:44.583 --> 01:06:46.459
It's a ride-along, Porter.

01:06:46.711 --> 01:06:49.462
Your piece of the pie
just got smaller.

01:06:49.714 --> 01:06:52.257
But don't worry,
I'll leave you some crust. Ha, ha.

01:06:52.425 --> 01:06:54.259
[CHUCKLES]

01:06:54.427 --> 01:06:56.720
LEARY: What are you waiting for?
Go get it.

01:06:57.096 --> 01:06:58.096
Go get our money.

01:07:00.683 --> 01:07:01.891
You guys do me a favor?

01:07:02.685 --> 01:07:03.935
We're here to help.

01:07:05.104 --> 01:07:08.773
They'll frisk me when I go in.
Would you hold on to this?

01:07:10.067 --> 01:07:11.484
Jesus.

01:07:11.902 --> 01:07:13.611
Just for a little while.

01:07:15.281 --> 01:07:16.865
Sure, Porter.

01:07:22.788 --> 01:07:24.247
Nice balance.

01:07:28.294 --> 01:07:29.627
Douche bag.

01:07:29.795 --> 01:07:31.296
[HICKS & LEARY CHUCKLE]

01:07:41.057 --> 01:07:42.766
Can I help you?

01:07:43.476 --> 01:07:46.478
- I want to see Mr. Carter.
- And who are you?

01:07:46.812 --> 01:07:49.272
Tell him I'm the guy
that whacked Val Resnick.

01:07:49.440 --> 01:07:50.732
I'm sorry, I don't...

01:07:50.900 --> 01:07:52.525
[RADIO CHATTERING]

01:07:52.693 --> 01:07:54.819
Didn't copy. Repeat.

01:07:58.491 --> 01:07:59.616
Right.

01:08:01.077 --> 01:08:04.829
Mr. Carter will see you.
Uh, turn around so I can frisk you.

01:08:07.583 --> 01:08:09.167
[DOOR BUZZES]

01:08:15.591 --> 01:08:18.676
[MEN GRUNTING]

01:08:22.014 --> 01:08:23.098
[SIGHS]

01:08:29.688 --> 01:08:31.648
Bravo. Sit down.

01:08:37.696 --> 01:08:40.156
My compliments.
They were two of my best.

01:08:40.366 --> 01:08:42.367
They lull too easy.

01:08:52.127 --> 01:08:53.877
You want something from me.

01:08:54.796 --> 01:08:58.299
Val Resnick gave you $130,000.

01:08:58.801 --> 01:09:00.718
He paid us.
It was a debt.

01:09:01.220 --> 01:09:03.930
$70,000 of it is mine.
I want it back.

01:09:06.015 --> 01:09:09.269
I'm sorry, but I seem to have
misplaced your name.

01:09:09.687 --> 01:09:11.895
- Porter.
- Porter. Right.

01:09:12.398 --> 01:09:14.691
I won't forget it again.

01:09:15.317 --> 01:09:18.027
The Outfit is not unreasonable.

01:09:18.529 --> 01:09:22.115
But no corporation would agree
to what you're asking.

01:09:22.366 --> 01:09:24.701
Will Fairfax give me my money?

01:09:27.328 --> 01:09:31.666
Resnick told you quite a bit.
Fairfax will say the same thing I have.

01:09:32.001 --> 01:09:34.711
We're not authorized
to do things like this.

01:09:34.920 --> 01:09:36.629
Who is?
Who makes the decisions?

01:09:37.256 --> 01:09:39.465
A committee would, in this case.

01:09:39.716 --> 01:09:43.094
You go high enough, you always come
to one man. Who?

01:09:46.265 --> 01:09:48.099
Yes.

01:09:48.267 --> 01:09:50.350
[MAN GRUNTING]

01:09:50.519 --> 01:09:52.979
[PHONE RINGS]

01:09:55.941 --> 01:09:59.027
[WOMAN OVER SPEAKER]: Mr. Bronson,
I have Mr. Carter on the line.

01:09:59.278 --> 01:10:01.070
Put him through.

01:10:01.280 --> 01:10:02.614
Go ahead, sir.

01:10:02.865 --> 01:10:04.324
Carter, how's business?

01:10:04.575 --> 01:10:06.951
CARTER: Good till now.
- You want to see me, Dad?

01:10:07.119 --> 01:10:08.912
Hang on, Carter.

01:10:09.371 --> 01:10:11.873
Look in that green box, Johnny.

01:10:18.297 --> 01:10:19.964
[CHUCKLES]

01:10:25.304 --> 01:10:26.888
Are you kidding me?

01:10:27.056 --> 01:10:29.974
Ha, ha. Is it the convertible?

01:10:30.226 --> 01:10:31.267
You thought I forgot.

01:10:32.144 --> 01:10:34.145
Whoo! Ha, ha!

01:10:34.313 --> 01:10:35.939
Happy birthday, son.

01:10:36.273 --> 01:10:40.235
[JOHNNY OVER SPEAKER]: This car?
Nick's got us ringside at the fight tonight.

01:10:40.402 --> 01:10:41.444
BRONSON:
It'll be good.

01:10:41.654 --> 01:10:43.238
My money's on Rankin.

01:10:43.489 --> 01:10:45.323
No, Hicks is favored.

01:10:46.158 --> 01:10:48.826
- That's got nothing to do with it.
- I got to go.

01:10:50.663 --> 01:10:51.913
Thanks.

01:10:52.248 --> 01:10:53.331
BRONSON:
Happy birthday.

01:10:54.166 --> 01:10:56.709
- Drive safe.
JOHNNY: You got it.

01:10:57.586 --> 01:10:58.962
BRONSON:
Sorry. What is it?

01:11:00.172 --> 01:11:04.384
I have a problem. There's a man
in my office with a gun...

01:11:04.760 --> 01:11:07.595
...who says he'll kill me
if we don't pay him...

01:11:07.846 --> 01:11:11.349
...$130,000 that one of our guys
stole from him.

01:11:12.017 --> 01:11:15.561
PORTER: It's 70. How much is
this guy Carter worth to you?

01:11:15.854 --> 01:11:16.854
What do you mean?

01:11:17.189 --> 01:11:19.440
Either I get my money
or I'll kill Carter.

01:11:19.942 --> 01:11:21.567
Are you threatening me?

01:11:21.860 --> 01:11:24.696
PORTER: I'm not threatening you.
I'm threatening Carter.

01:11:25.990 --> 01:11:28.825
BRONSON:
An audacious man. Who are you?

01:11:28.993 --> 01:11:30.493
[SCOFFS]

01:11:31.328 --> 01:11:32.996
My money, yes or no?

01:11:33.706 --> 01:11:34.747
No.

01:11:36.709 --> 01:11:38.626
[GRUNTS]

01:11:39.420 --> 01:11:40.545
Carter?

01:11:40.713 --> 01:11:43.923
- Oh.
- Carter?

01:11:45.467 --> 01:11:47.218
Carter?

01:11:47.886 --> 01:11:49.887
What's going on there?

01:11:50.180 --> 01:11:54.434
You just don't get it,
do you, you dumb fuck?

01:11:54.685 --> 01:11:56.728
Carter, talk to me.

01:11:58.647 --> 01:11:59.897
Carter?

01:12:00.065 --> 01:12:03.067
PORTER: Call Fairfax and tell him
I just croaked Carter.

01:12:03.319 --> 01:12:06.612
And he's next. After that,
I'm coming to get you.

01:12:07.364 --> 01:12:09.449
BRONSON:
Are you out of your fucking mind?

01:12:10.034 --> 01:12:12.702
You just dug your own grave.

01:12:20.252 --> 01:12:23.046
- I don't see any cash.
- They write you a check?

01:12:23.547 --> 01:12:26.049
I have to go and see another guy.

01:12:26.342 --> 01:12:27.342
HICKS:
Last one.

01:12:27.551 --> 01:12:31.512
Then we got a dead woman and assault
to talk to you about.

01:12:31.764 --> 01:12:35.224
That means more paperwork.
And we don't like paperwork.

01:12:35.601 --> 01:12:37.268
STEGMAN:
Damn shame, Porter.

01:12:37.519 --> 01:12:40.188
But don't let the bastards
get you down. Ha, ha.

01:12:41.273 --> 01:12:43.941
That's right. Don't give up.

01:12:46.904 --> 01:12:48.196
Can I have my piece?

01:12:48.614 --> 01:12:49.864
Oh, yeah.

01:12:54.828 --> 01:12:56.454
[SIGHS]

01:12:58.374 --> 01:12:59.499
LEARY:
Nice roscoe.

01:13:00.626 --> 01:13:02.335
Heavy enough to be a nutcracker.

01:13:02.586 --> 01:13:04.921
We'll be in touch, Rocky.

01:13:06.632 --> 01:13:08.883
LEARY:
Keep up the good work.

01:13:10.469 --> 01:13:14.889
PORTER: Nobody likes a monkey
on their back. I had three.

01:13:15.432 --> 01:13:17.850
And they were cramping my style.

01:13:18.102 --> 01:13:20.770
I was going to
have to lighten the load.

01:13:22.314 --> 01:13:23.606
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:13:51.635 --> 01:13:52.677
[DOOR OPENS]

01:13:57.224 --> 01:13:58.474
Porter?

01:13:58.851 --> 01:13:59.934
Where have you been?

01:14:00.144 --> 01:14:03.354
I was taking care of business.
Evening up the odds.

01:14:04.982 --> 01:14:07.984
They won't stop until they kill us,
will they?

01:14:10.612 --> 01:14:11.654
No.

01:14:12.698 --> 01:14:14.157
[SCOFFS]

01:14:17.286 --> 01:14:18.953
I'm sorry.

01:14:19.955 --> 01:14:21.664
I'm sorry I got you involved.

01:14:24.543 --> 01:14:26.961
So why did you?

01:14:28.964 --> 01:14:32.592
You're a clever guy.
You didn't need me.

01:14:35.012 --> 01:14:36.721
So why did you?

01:14:38.849 --> 01:14:40.892
Yeah, you're right.

01:14:43.061 --> 01:14:47.398
When I came back,
I came back here with nothing.

01:14:50.235 --> 01:14:52.320
No life. No hope.

01:14:54.364 --> 01:14:57.450
You were the only good thing
that hadn't been taken.

01:15:01.163 --> 01:15:03.080
I couldn't stay away.

01:15:05.167 --> 01:15:08.377
I had to see you to make sure
I wasn't in hell.

01:15:11.048 --> 01:15:13.007
So why don't we get out of here?

01:15:14.218 --> 01:15:15.760
- We can't.
- Why?

01:15:16.011 --> 01:15:19.055
They won't stop until they bury us.

01:15:22.226 --> 01:15:26.145
- So?
- So we bury them first.

01:16:11.900 --> 01:16:13.734
I should have quit.

01:16:21.159 --> 01:16:23.327
I should have driven you
somewhere else.

01:16:30.752 --> 01:16:33.254
[CROWD CHEERING AND SHOUTING]

01:16:39.511 --> 01:16:41.012
[BELL RINGS]

01:16:41.179 --> 01:16:44.015
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:17:09.958 --> 01:17:11.500
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

01:17:14.630 --> 01:17:16.047
That's me!

01:17:17.716 --> 01:17:20.384
[ALL CHATTERING]

01:17:24.014 --> 01:17:26.015
[BELL RINGS]

01:17:31.480 --> 01:17:33.939
Happy birthday, Johnny.

01:17:36.193 --> 01:17:39.070
[ALL CHATTERING]

01:17:39.237 --> 01:17:41.405
MAN 1: You are the man!
MAN 2: This is your night.

01:17:41.573 --> 01:17:43.574
ROSIE:
Hey, Johnny.

01:17:50.082 --> 01:17:52.041
I'm your birthday present.

01:17:53.210 --> 01:17:55.878
MAN: Who's that?
JOHNNY: You sons of bitches!

01:17:56.088 --> 01:17:58.339
MAN:
We didn't do it.

01:17:58.507 --> 01:18:00.591
Ha, ha. Dude, she's so hot.

01:18:00.759 --> 01:18:03.844
Oh, man, she's so fine.
You're all over it. Go!

01:18:04.096 --> 01:18:06.722
MAN 2: Look at this guy!
Dad's really hooking him up.

01:18:06.932 --> 01:18:10.059
Boy, you are cute, aren't you?

01:18:11.353 --> 01:18:15.231
You must have some pretty
wonderful friends, Johnny.

01:18:15.774 --> 01:18:18.567
Wealthy too, because I'm not cheap.

01:18:23.115 --> 01:18:25.116
Don't wait up, boys.

01:18:25.867 --> 01:18:28.411
I promise he won't be home
before midnight.

01:18:28.578 --> 01:18:30.705
[JOHNNY LAUGHS]

01:18:30.872 --> 01:18:32.915
Ha, ha! See you!

01:18:34.918 --> 01:18:36.711
Damn! Ha-ha-ha!

01:18:42.217 --> 01:18:45.386
[JOHNNY MOANING]

01:18:48.473 --> 01:18:50.141
JOHNNY: Mm.
- That's a good boy.

01:18:52.561 --> 01:18:55.479
Yeah, right there. Ha, ha.

01:19:06.324 --> 01:19:07.867
Relax.

01:19:08.493 --> 01:19:11.120
Who's the professional here?

01:19:11.580 --> 01:19:13.706
So go with it.

01:19:13.957 --> 01:19:16.959
I promise you won't regret it.

01:19:17.669 --> 01:19:19.462
There, baby.

01:19:20.756 --> 01:19:22.214
Oh.

01:19:23.383 --> 01:19:24.800
[ROSIE SIGHS]

01:19:30.056 --> 01:19:31.807
Hello?

01:19:32.601 --> 01:19:34.894
[B.B. KING'S "THE THRILL IS GONE"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

01:19:35.061 --> 01:19:37.438
Relax, kid,
no one'll get hurt.

01:19:41.026 --> 01:19:44.069
Get hurt?
What's he talking about?

01:19:44.237 --> 01:19:46.489
Shh.

01:20:00.045 --> 01:20:02.338
MAN:
Good to have you back, Mr. Fairfax.

01:20:02.547 --> 01:20:07.009
I wish I could say the same. I was
swimming with dolphins this morning.

01:20:08.553 --> 01:20:12.348
Easy! It's genuine alligator.
What's the matter with you?

01:20:12.557 --> 01:20:14.558
Sorry, Mr. Fairfax.

01:20:15.602 --> 01:20:18.479
CHARLIE: Hello, Mr. Fairfax.
- How's it going, Charlie?

01:20:20.232 --> 01:20:24.527
Porter and Fairfax.
That'll be a short conversation.

01:20:29.241 --> 01:20:33.702
Between us and our neighborhood cops,
I'd say we got him well covered, huh?

01:20:36.081 --> 01:20:37.081
FAIRFAX:
Walter, wake up.

01:20:39.626 --> 01:20:41.085
Walter.

01:20:41.503 --> 01:20:42.628
Wake up!

01:20:43.755 --> 01:20:45.840
Keep those bags up, boys.

01:20:46.091 --> 01:20:47.174
Come on.

01:20:48.176 --> 01:20:49.885
Who the hell are you?

01:20:50.595 --> 01:20:53.097
I'm the reason you're home early.

01:20:54.766 --> 01:20:55.850
You're Porter?

01:20:56.434 --> 01:20:59.645
That's it. Keep them up
or I'll drill you.

01:21:04.526 --> 01:21:07.444
What will you have me do?
Uh, stand on my head?

01:21:09.030 --> 01:21:14.076
No. I want you to do me a favor.
Call Mr. Bronson.

01:21:14.286 --> 01:21:16.370
See what we can do
about getting my money back.

01:21:16.538 --> 01:21:18.622
[SIGHS]

01:21:18.790 --> 01:21:20.833
He let Carter die.

01:21:21.877 --> 01:21:24.044
That poor bastard's
better off dead anyway.

01:21:24.212 --> 01:21:25.838
[CHUCKLES]

01:21:26.006 --> 01:21:27.923
He'd probably let me die too.

01:21:28.133 --> 01:21:30.634
With Carter,
he thought I was bluffing.

01:21:31.761 --> 01:21:35.306
Try him. He might be more
receptive than you think.

01:21:37.475 --> 01:21:38.809
All right.

01:21:40.145 --> 01:21:41.478
You two are fired.

01:21:45.025 --> 01:21:48.152
Hello? Well, it's like this.

01:21:48.486 --> 01:21:51.739
I'm in my living room.
There's a man named Porter...

01:21:51.990 --> 01:21:54.992
...who says that
he, uh, expects you to pay him.

01:21:57.662 --> 01:21:59.246
Of course.

01:21:59.497 --> 01:22:01.123
He wants to talk to you.

01:22:01.333 --> 01:22:02.791
Put it on the speaker.

01:22:02.959 --> 01:22:05.002
[MEN GROANING]

01:22:07.797 --> 01:22:10.674
- This is Porter.
[BRONSON OVER SPEAKER]: You got balls.

01:22:11.176 --> 01:22:14.428
You've proven to be a pain
in the ass. A mosquito.

01:22:15.347 --> 01:22:17.973
To get rid of you,
I'll swat you with 130 grand.

01:22:18.141 --> 01:22:19.516
[SCOFFS]

01:22:19.684 --> 01:22:21.018
It's not a hund...

01:22:23.855 --> 01:22:26.357
- What the hell are you doing?
BRONSON: Fairfax?

01:22:26.608 --> 01:22:29.985
It's all right. He's just
killing my alligator bags...

01:22:30.195 --> 01:22:32.738
...and shooting holes in my suits.

01:22:33.365 --> 01:22:35.032
That's mean, man!

01:22:35.325 --> 01:22:37.534
You aren't listening.
It's not 130...

01:22:37.702 --> 01:22:38.744
BRONSON:
No, you listen.

01:22:39.120 --> 01:22:42.581
You'll get your money,
but you'll never live to enjoy it.

01:22:42.791 --> 01:22:44.708
PORTER:
You let me worry about that.

01:22:44.876 --> 01:22:47.753
I want you to deliver
the money yourself.

01:22:49.172 --> 01:22:51.006
You're one hell of an optimist.

01:22:51.216 --> 01:22:54.176
What makes you think
I'll deliver it myself?

01:22:54.803 --> 01:22:57.304
If you don't,
you'll never see Johnny again.

01:22:58.974 --> 01:23:01.308
Didn't come home last night, did he?

01:23:01.518 --> 01:23:04.520
He's a good-looking kid,
but you indulge him too much.

01:23:04.729 --> 01:23:06.271
I told him so.

01:23:07.065 --> 01:23:09.692
Bullshit. You haven't got him.

01:23:10.068 --> 01:23:13.779
- You're not that stupid.
- My dad never bought me a Ferrari.

01:23:14.030 --> 01:23:16.240
I had to steal my first one.

01:23:16.533 --> 01:23:19.159
Nice inscription on the key chain.

01:23:19.411 --> 01:23:21.078
A little sappy.
Want me to read it?

01:23:22.205 --> 01:23:25.457
You're dead.
Nobody fucks with my family.

01:23:25.625 --> 01:23:26.709
You hear me?

01:23:27.752 --> 01:23:29.128
You're a dead man.

01:23:29.421 --> 01:23:33.173
That's Johnny, unless you
turn up with the money.

01:23:34.884 --> 01:23:37.511
Is that a yes? Hmm?

01:23:37.679 --> 01:23:39.346
What? Cat got your crotch?

01:23:41.224 --> 01:23:43.684
Some decisions are hard, Mr. Bronson.

01:23:43.852 --> 01:23:44.935
Where?

01:23:46.104 --> 01:23:47.187
I'll let you know.

01:23:47.605 --> 01:23:49.648
I'll be in touch.

01:23:51.276 --> 01:23:52.484
[LINE BUZZING]

01:23:52.652 --> 01:23:54.111
[SIGHS]

01:23:54.279 --> 01:23:55.696
[HANGS UP PHONE]

01:23:55.864 --> 01:23:58.949
You just signed your own
death warrant for $130,000.

01:23:59.159 --> 01:24:01.368
I don't get that. What is it?

01:24:02.287 --> 01:24:03.829
The principle or something, huh?

01:24:05.373 --> 01:24:09.168
Stop it, I'm getting misty.
And tell him it's 70.

01:24:10.962 --> 01:24:13.881
Seventy?
What do you mean, it's only 70?

01:24:14.132 --> 01:24:15.924
- Only 70,000?
MEN: Unh!

01:24:16.593 --> 01:24:18.844
My suits are worth more than that!

01:24:21.056 --> 01:24:22.473
HICKS:
Oh, man!

01:24:22.766 --> 01:24:26.560
Listen to this:
"Ocean Ray Sundancer.

01:24:27.228 --> 01:24:30.397
Icemaker. Camper canvas.

01:24:30.899 --> 01:24:32.733
Vacuum-flush head.

01:24:33.943 --> 01:24:35.319
Eighty thousand bucks."

01:24:37.322 --> 01:24:39.114
He ain't going to have it.

01:24:39.407 --> 01:24:40.449
You want to bet?

01:24:40.658 --> 01:24:44.870
No, I don't want to bet.
I'm out 150 already.

01:24:46.081 --> 01:24:48.749
150 ain't getting my damn boat.

01:24:49.000 --> 01:24:51.376
- He better come down with something.
- Hey, hey, hey.

01:24:52.629 --> 01:24:54.129
Hicks. Leary.

01:24:54.464 --> 01:24:58.258
We're Holland and Van Owen.
Internal Affairs.

01:25:01.304 --> 01:25:03.347
Back off.
We're on a stakeout.

01:25:04.432 --> 01:25:06.141
Step out of the car, please.

01:25:06.810 --> 01:25:10.062
- What for?
- Step out of the car, detectives.

01:25:18.863 --> 01:25:20.322
[SIGHS]

01:25:23.701 --> 01:25:25.327
What the hell's going on?

01:25:25.912 --> 01:25:26.954
I don't know.

01:25:27.789 --> 01:25:29.039
Is this your badge?

01:25:29.666 --> 01:25:32.042
The one you reported missing?

01:25:34.045 --> 01:25:35.087
Where'd you find it?

01:25:35.505 --> 01:25:36.922
Where did you lose it?

01:25:41.553 --> 01:25:42.928
HOLLAND:
Does this belong to you?

01:25:45.014 --> 01:25:47.057
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:25:49.310 --> 01:25:50.561
It's Porter. Follow him.

01:25:51.479 --> 01:25:52.771
I got that motherfucker.

01:26:06.244 --> 01:26:07.661
Hey!

01:26:14.419 --> 01:26:15.544
Get in.

01:26:22.510 --> 01:26:23.594
Close the door.

01:26:28.349 --> 01:26:30.017
Set the roscoe on the floor.

01:26:32.478 --> 01:26:33.979
Slow!

01:26:38.401 --> 01:26:41.737
I'm going to turn you in
to the Outfit for a reward.

01:26:42.447 --> 01:26:46.950
Maybe they'll ask me to join,
and I'll be on easy street.

01:26:47.452 --> 01:26:49.578
Medical. Dental.

01:26:50.622 --> 01:26:52.748
I'm going to walk you right in.

01:26:53.291 --> 01:26:55.667
Porter on the hoof.

01:26:56.753 --> 01:27:00.547
Unless you get rambunctious.
Then I'll take care of you...

01:27:05.011 --> 01:27:07.095
You're not going to kill me, are you?

01:27:07.472 --> 01:27:09.056
[PORTER GROWLING]

01:27:09.224 --> 01:27:10.307
[STEGMAN GRUNTING]

01:27:10.475 --> 01:27:12.726
[TIRES SCREECH]

01:27:15.104 --> 01:27:16.355
Let him go!

01:27:16.522 --> 01:27:17.773
[GUN COCKS]

01:27:17.941 --> 01:27:18.982
Now.

01:27:23.571 --> 01:27:24.821
[GUNS COCKS]

01:27:24.989 --> 01:27:26.448
Hubba, hubba, hubba.

01:27:29.285 --> 01:27:31.620
[STEGMAN GRUNTING]

01:27:42.840 --> 01:27:44.841
[STEGMAN GROANS]

01:27:48.513 --> 01:27:50.389
[ALL GRUNT]

01:27:58.940 --> 01:28:00.607
[PORTER GRUNTING]

01:28:07.865 --> 01:28:09.157
[LAUGHS]

01:28:09.325 --> 01:28:10.534
[GASPS]

01:28:11.703 --> 01:28:13.036
I, uh...

01:28:13.204 --> 01:28:14.579
[GRUNTS]

01:28:22.213 --> 01:28:23.505
[GASPS]

01:28:28.511 --> 01:28:31.346
[PEARL CHUCKLES]

01:28:37.854 --> 01:28:40.480
[GUN CLICKING]

01:28:52.410 --> 01:28:54.077
[GUN CLICKS]

01:28:56.748 --> 01:28:58.623
Who are you?
What are you doing?

01:28:58.791 --> 01:28:59.916
Fat boy!

01:29:01.252 --> 01:29:03.045
Yeah, I'm talking to you.

01:29:03.755 --> 01:29:05.922
[GRUNTS]

01:29:16.976 --> 01:29:18.727
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:29:23.232 --> 01:29:24.608
[TIRES SCREECHING]

01:29:27.653 --> 01:29:28.779
Mm.

01:29:32.241 --> 01:29:34.618
Ah, stop it. Stop it.

01:29:35.119 --> 01:29:36.745
I hate this. I hate it!

01:29:41.042 --> 01:29:44.127
Look at this stinking place!
Porter, what's the matter with you?

01:29:44.295 --> 01:29:45.962
[GRUNTS]

01:29:46.130 --> 01:29:48.799
Tell us where he is
so we can get out of here, huh?

01:29:49.258 --> 01:29:50.384
Come on.

01:30:00.061 --> 01:30:01.144
Too late now.

01:30:05.316 --> 01:30:07.567
He doesn't want to say anything.

01:30:07.985 --> 01:30:11.071
He just wants to get himself beat up,
that's all.

01:30:16.077 --> 01:30:17.494
Here it is.

01:30:17.745 --> 01:30:19.371
130,000.

01:30:23.418 --> 01:30:25.794
That's as close as
you'll ever get to it.

01:30:26.170 --> 01:30:27.796
I'll make you a deal.

01:30:28.506 --> 01:30:31.633
Tell me where John is,
and I'll finish you quick.

01:30:31.843 --> 01:30:35.429
You won't have to find out
what your left ball tastes like.

01:30:39.267 --> 01:30:43.937
But if there's even a bruise on him,
I'll make this last three weeks.

01:30:44.689 --> 01:30:48.608
I'll give you a blood transfusion
to keep you alive.

01:30:52.864 --> 01:30:53.989
Where is he?

01:30:54.157 --> 01:30:56.450
[SIGHS]

01:31:15.553 --> 01:31:17.762
[PORTER COUGHS]

01:31:20.057 --> 01:31:21.558
[SIGHS]

01:31:26.147 --> 01:31:27.230
I'm waiting.

01:31:32.403 --> 01:31:34.279
This piggy went to the market.

01:31:39.702 --> 01:31:40.744
[SCREAMS]

01:31:41.913 --> 01:31:43.580
[PORTER GRUNTING]

01:31:48.753 --> 01:31:49.878
I'm listening.

01:31:50.046 --> 01:31:51.630
[GRUNTING]

01:31:51.797 --> 01:31:53.507
[GASPING]

01:32:01.432 --> 01:32:02.724
This piggy stayed home.

01:32:08.147 --> 01:32:10.232
Starting to look like roast beef.

01:32:11.692 --> 01:32:13.235
[GASPING]

01:32:13.778 --> 01:32:15.362
Eight to go.

01:32:16.030 --> 01:32:17.531
Then it's your knees.

01:32:17.949 --> 01:32:20.408
You can guess where we go from there.

01:32:21.244 --> 01:32:22.285
Where is he?

01:32:30.127 --> 01:32:31.962
Okay. Okay.

01:32:34.632 --> 01:32:36.216
Twenty-four...

01:32:37.301 --> 01:32:39.010
Twenty-four Fielding.

01:32:40.638 --> 01:32:41.763
Apartment 11.

01:32:42.974 --> 01:32:44.766
[SOBBING]

01:32:45.476 --> 01:32:48.144
You'll understand
if I don't trust you.

01:32:51.065 --> 01:32:54.192
Put him in the trunk.
We'll take him along.

01:32:55.361 --> 01:32:56.820
BRONSON'S HEAVY:
Let's go, tough guy.

01:33:03.119 --> 01:33:20.218
[GRUNTING]

01:33:24.682 --> 01:33:26.683
FAIRFAX:
You two watch the front.

01:33:28.102 --> 01:33:29.894
[GRUNTING]

01:33:39.196 --> 01:33:41.156
Fuck! Come on, Porter.

01:33:43.534 --> 01:33:44.701
[DOG GROWLS]

01:33:48.831 --> 01:33:50.457
Hey, give me a light.

01:33:50.625 --> 01:33:52.500
[PORTER PANTING]

01:33:56.672 --> 01:33:58.465
[SIGHS]

01:34:00.134 --> 01:34:02.218
[GRUNTING]

01:34:34.168 --> 01:34:35.669
[GRUNTS]

01:34:52.353 --> 01:34:54.062
[MAN GRUNTS]

01:34:56.023 --> 01:34:59.275
[PHONE RINGING]

01:35:11.122 --> 01:35:15.125
BRONSON: What the hell's going on?
- You were right not to trust me.

01:35:15.292 --> 01:35:17.377
[BOMB CLICKING]

01:35:40.985 --> 01:35:42.527
Help me.

01:35:44.822 --> 01:35:46.156
Get out!

01:35:46.782 --> 01:35:49.659
[PORTER GROANING]

01:35:53.956 --> 01:35:55.957
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:36:12.516 --> 01:36:15.185
[HORN HONKING OUTSIDE]

01:36:26.572 --> 01:36:27.864
[GRUNTS]

01:36:28.032 --> 01:36:31.284
Come on, Porter.
It's been fun. See you later.

01:36:31.702 --> 01:36:34.204
Get back here! You bitch!

01:36:35.039 --> 01:36:36.581
Come on, Porter.
Let's go.

01:36:37.041 --> 01:36:39.667
- What took you so long?
- Hi, Rosie.

01:36:39.835 --> 01:36:41.294
[GROANS]

01:36:41.462 --> 01:36:42.879
ROSIE:
Come on, Porter.

01:36:45.549 --> 01:36:46.674
Get in.

01:36:47.384 --> 01:36:48.802
Good boy.

01:36:52.556 --> 01:36:53.640
What happened?

01:36:54.892 --> 01:36:56.059
I got hammered.

01:36:56.977 --> 01:36:58.019
You okay?

01:36:59.522 --> 01:37:01.064
Yeah.

01:37:09.240 --> 01:37:12.450
- You got it.
- Piece of cake.

01:37:14.870 --> 01:37:16.746
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:37:16.914 --> 01:37:18.039
Where to?

01:37:20.417 --> 01:37:22.752
Just drive, baby.

01:37:26.924 --> 01:37:29.425
PORTER:
We were going for breakfast...

01:37:30.010 --> 01:37:31.970
...in Canada.

01:37:33.055 --> 01:37:34.889
We made a deal:

01:37:35.099 --> 01:37:37.225
If she'd stop hooking...

01:37:37.434 --> 01:37:39.853
...I'd stop shooting people.

01:37:41.939 --> 01:37:44.232
Maybe we were aiming high.

01:41:15.986 --> 01:41:17.987
[ENGLISH SDH]

